WEBVTT

00:10.301 --> 00:12.553
Sorry. I'm sorry.

00:12.762 --> 00:15.629
I was on a call with the mayor,
then Tess pushed my deadline.

00:15.807 --> 00:17.092
I know we said 8, so I'm—

00:17.267 --> 00:18.723
Right on time...

00:18.893 --> 00:19.928
...for you.

00:21.479 --> 00:24.095
I bet even you couldn't run faster
in these heels.

00:24.274 --> 00:26.765
I wouldn't look nearly as good.

00:27.027 --> 00:30.645
What do you say we take your shoes
and my sport coat and get a nice dinner?

00:30.822 --> 00:33.188
Smallville,
you're not wearing a sport coat.

00:37.495 --> 00:38.826
-Show-off.
-Listen...

00:38.997 --> 00:41.739
...why don't we get something to eat
at the new place?

00:41.916 --> 00:44.749
The place that requires reservations
six months in advance?

00:44.919 --> 00:47.410
Nice thought, Romeo,
but we'll never get a table.

00:49.090 --> 00:51.547
Never know unless we ask.
I hope the answer is yes.

00:53.178 --> 00:55.134
If we're lucky enough
to snag a cancellation...

00:55.305 --> 00:59.093
...with the VRA's latest no-fun policy,
we'll have to leave before dessert.

00:59.309 --> 01:00.970
Listen, we—

01:01.186 --> 01:04.974
We can't let a curfew prevent us from
having fun with the time we do have.

01:06.983 --> 01:08.314
[CLARK SIGHS]

01:11.905 --> 01:15.523
Even if I have to run to Madrid,
I'll get you churros and hot chocolate.

01:16.326 --> 01:20.285
Why don't we just go home,
skip right to the delicious doughnuts...

01:20.455 --> 01:24.164
...and we can pretend for one night
that the world hasn't gone totally crazy?

01:24.334 --> 01:26.416
The government
has taken a tougher stance...

01:26.586 --> 01:29.578
...since they upgraded our status
from vigilante to terrorist.

01:29.756 --> 01:32.873
The VRA's not just raining
on the heroes' parade anymore.

01:33.051 --> 01:36.635
We are gonna need an ark
to survive this hate-ﬁlled ﬂood.

01:36.846 --> 01:40.259
But unlike the rest of Metropolis,
I haven't forgotten the real heroes.

01:40.433 --> 01:44.472
And there is one in particular
that I would love to snuggle up with...

01:44.646 --> 01:47.137
...away from the searchlights.

01:47.357 --> 01:49.643
Yeah, we should probably, uh,
just go home.

01:49.859 --> 01:51.019
But wait a second.

01:52.487 --> 01:55.149
I think I hear a situation
that needs saving.

01:55.365 --> 01:56.400
I'll be right back.

01:58.118 --> 02:01.110
[PHONE RINGING]

02:08.753 --> 02:10.038
Did you save the day?

02:10.213 --> 02:13.080
CLARK [OVER PHONE]:
I don't know yet. Look up.

02:31.276 --> 02:32.732
[CH UCKLES]

02:39.367 --> 02:40.698
[CH UCKLES]

02:48.918 --> 02:52.081
You don't make it easy
to ask a simple question.

02:53.548 --> 02:57.040
But that's what makes you you.

02:57.927 --> 03:00.794
The woman I wanna spend my life with.

03:01.598 --> 03:05.090
The woman that I love.

03:05.518 --> 03:06.803
[GASPS]

03:11.482 --> 03:15.851
Lois Lane, will you marry me?

03:19.574 --> 03:20.939
Yes.

04:36.192 --> 04:38.274
Hey, Ollie, it's Lois.

04:38.444 --> 04:42.028
I don't know if you've talked with
Clark yet, but we have a big update.

04:42.198 --> 04:45.440
You'd be one of the ﬁrst to know
if you'd pick up the phone...

04:45.618 --> 04:47.529
...which nobody is doing.

04:47.704 --> 04:52.243
Oh, hey, Gestapo's on the other line.
Gotta go.

04:54.252 --> 04:56.334
Keys, coins, phone.

04:58.047 --> 04:59.378
[LOIS CLEARS THROAT]

05:01.467 --> 05:05.551
Oh. Oops, I forgot to give you this.
I hope it doesn't set off any alarms.

05:06.723 --> 05:10.466
-Next.
-Really? Nothing? Huh.

05:10.643 --> 05:12.224
GUARD 1:
Keys, coins, phone.

05:17.233 --> 05:18.939
GUARD 2:
Go ahead.

05:23.364 --> 05:24.945
CLERK:
Miss Lane?

05:53.686 --> 05:57.349
Dr. Livingstone, I presume.
What, the safari got sidetracked?

05:57.523 --> 06:00.185
I haven't exactly left for Africa yet.

06:00.943 --> 06:02.604
Question, 002.

06:02.779 --> 06:04.019
You and Oliver.

06:05.114 --> 06:08.106
You're busy with work
and he's really busy with work.

06:08.284 --> 06:09.820
And then there's...

06:10.453 --> 06:12.944
...well, all his other responsibilities.

06:14.665 --> 06:16.166
As a rich playboy?

06:16.334 --> 06:18.450
Very time-consuming.

06:18.628 --> 06:22.962
So I'm guessing that between the two
of you, things must get...

06:23.716 --> 06:24.796
...complicated?

06:26.135 --> 06:28.000
Lois, what exactly
are we talking about?

06:31.140 --> 06:33.973
Chloe, what really happened
between Clark and Lana?

06:35.686 --> 06:39.349
She couldn't make the sacriﬁces
he needed, could she?

06:46.823 --> 06:50.987
Let's just say Lana wasn't the one
fated to be in Clark's life.

07:05.550 --> 07:09.839
I don't know how you do it, Chlo.
It's like you can see the future.

07:17.603 --> 07:19.719
Honestly, I don't know
why you people are grumbling.

07:19.897 --> 07:21.762
Security's for our own good.

07:23.985 --> 07:27.193
Oh, my God. Lois Lane.

07:27.780 --> 07:28.895
Are you expecting?

07:30.241 --> 07:31.356
[CH UCKLES]

07:31.534 --> 07:35.243
Spread that rumor
and you can expect my ﬁst in your face.

07:37.582 --> 07:40.790
When I got engaged, I thought
my happily-ever-after was all set.

07:41.377 --> 07:45.211
But every storybook romance
doesn't have a fairy-tale ending.

07:46.215 --> 07:48.467
So now I'm married to my work,
which is ﬁne.

07:48.634 --> 07:51.091
-Cat—
-With the VRA cleaning up our streets...

07:51.262 --> 07:53.503
...you don't have any heroes
to write about.

07:54.015 --> 07:57.303
That's okay, you can use the extra time
to work on your domestic side.

07:57.518 --> 07:58.553
Snickerdoodle?

08:00.062 --> 08:01.893
Am I interrupting something?

08:02.607 --> 08:05.815
Just a little girl talk
with the future Mrs. Clark Kent.

08:06.277 --> 08:07.312
Oh.

08:07.820 --> 08:11.938
I hope your new responsibilities at home
don't interfere with your ones here.

08:13.034 --> 08:14.570
Neither of which concern you.

08:14.744 --> 08:17.076
Oh, sorry.

08:18.748 --> 08:20.955
The VRA's not the only one
increasing security.

08:21.125 --> 08:23.662
l'm reprogramming
Watchtower's retina scan tonight...

08:23.836 --> 08:26.293
...and you're up at 9. Don't be late.

08:34.430 --> 08:35.670
Lois.

08:35.848 --> 08:38.931
-Retina scan?
-Yeah. Nine.

08:39.101 --> 08:42.468
You know, she should be better
at crossing her T's, not her wires.

08:46.567 --> 08:48.432
ALL:
Surprise.

08:48.611 --> 08:50.101
COURTNEY:
Congratulations, you two.

08:50.279 --> 08:52.736
OLIVER: Ha, ha.
You should see the look on your....

08:52.907 --> 08:55.444
TESS:
Congratulations.

08:57.078 --> 09:00.366
So I think anyone who commits
themselves to a lifetime of Lois...

09:00.581 --> 09:02.822
...deserves all the moral support
they can get.

09:03.000 --> 09:05.161
There's nothing more that I would like...

09:05.336 --> 09:07.827
...than to be courtside
at the event of the decade...

09:08.005 --> 09:11.463
...but now that the government's
conﬁrmed I blew up their facilities—

09:11.634 --> 09:15.377
-Not everyone believes propaganda.
-The whole world thinks I'm a terrorist.

09:15.596 --> 09:18.963
It's not exactly something you want
on your Fortune 500 bio...

09:19.308 --> 09:21.299
...or at your wedding, so....

09:21.477 --> 09:24.969
That's too bad, because I was just about
to invite you to be my best man.

09:25.147 --> 09:28.014
You're the guy who stands next to me
on the worst days.

09:28.192 --> 09:30.228
And I want you there
for the best one too.

09:31.988 --> 09:34.604
Hey, you kidding? Absolutely.
Thank you.

09:35.992 --> 09:40.156
All I can say is, when it comes
to planning the wedding, just nod.

09:40.329 --> 09:41.830
-Ha, ha.
-A lot.

09:41.998 --> 09:45.240
You would know. You married Shayera,
what, a hundred times now?

09:45.459 --> 09:46.790
I've heard of relationships...

09:46.961 --> 09:49.498
...that withstand the test of time.
That's remarkable.

09:49.672 --> 09:53.039
Or not, I suppose, for you.

09:53.843 --> 09:55.174
[CLARK CHUCKLES]

09:55.344 --> 09:57.175
COURTNEY: Aw.
EMIL: Are those prescription...?

09:57.346 --> 10:00.338
That sounds like a proposal
only Clark could pull off.

10:01.017 --> 10:02.928
Soon to be.

10:05.521 --> 10:07.728
-Hey.
-Hi.

10:09.275 --> 10:12.893
Even though I married Shayera
a hundred times...

10:13.070 --> 10:16.028
...I had to lose her that many as well.

10:17.783 --> 10:18.818
[CARTER CLEARS THROAT]

10:18.993 --> 10:22.281
Now, I know I don't usually
get all warm and fuzzy...

10:22.747 --> 10:24.703
...but I am sorry.

10:26.542 --> 10:28.373
About Chloe.

10:32.965 --> 10:34.546
-Not gonna hug me, are you?
-No.

10:34.717 --> 10:36.082
Okay.

10:36.594 --> 10:41.805
I'm just saying, I understand
that it's at times like these...

10:42.183 --> 10:44.469
...you miss them most.

10:48.731 --> 10:51.564
Well, let's hope they never
have to feel that kind of loss.

10:51.734 --> 10:54.976
No relationship can avoid
that possibility...

10:55.196 --> 10:59.690
...but if I've learned anything
in the last, oh, 3000 years...

11:00.242 --> 11:03.450
...it's that fear should never decide love.

11:05.831 --> 11:07.571
Well said.

11:08.417 --> 11:14.333
All right. So while there is still plenty of
champagne, I'd like to propose a toast.

11:14.507 --> 11:16.748
To the happy couple,
who ﬁnally ﬁgured out...

11:16.926 --> 11:19.588
...what we've all known
for a very long time now.

11:21.472 --> 11:23.463
-You are destined to be together.
EMIL: True.

11:23.641 --> 11:24.972
CARTER: Hear, hear.
EMIL: Cheers.

11:25.142 --> 11:27.224
COURTNEY: You're gonna be so happy.
TESS: Congrats.

11:27.395 --> 11:28.430
EMIL:
To Lois and Clark.

11:30.606 --> 11:33.598
[HELICOPTER DRONING]

11:37.613 --> 11:39.854
WOMAN:
Aah! Help! Help!

11:40.074 --> 11:41.189
[WOMAN WHIMPERING]

11:41.367 --> 11:42.652
Help!

11:42.827 --> 11:45.409
[OLIVER & MAN GRUNTING]

11:55.339 --> 11:59.548
-Now I got you, huh?
-Hey, that's Oliver Queen, the outlaw.

11:59.760 --> 12:02.297
Hold on a second here.
I'm not the bad guy.

12:02.471 --> 12:05.634
He's lying.
He came at me out of nowhere.

12:05.808 --> 12:08.971
Hey, that's not how it works in our city.
Not anymore!

12:09.854 --> 12:11.264
[GRUNTING]

12:25.453 --> 12:27.114
[COURTNEY GRUNTS]

12:27.788 --> 12:29.494
COURTNEY:
Back off!

12:30.166 --> 12:31.827
Hey.

12:39.008 --> 12:40.669
COURTNEY:
We gotta get out of here.

12:48.184 --> 12:49.219
[COURTNEY GRUNTS]

12:59.987 --> 13:03.855
MAN [ON BULLHORN]: Blue team,
take the front. Red squad, ﬂank them in.

13:09.872 --> 13:11.578
POLICEMAN 1: Yeah.
POLICEMAN 2: Go.

13:20.549 --> 13:22.881
Watching the sunrise
from the Daily Planet globe.

13:23.052 --> 13:25.418
Talk about making a girl feel
on top of the world.

13:25.596 --> 13:28.929
Just because our party was over
didn't mean our night had to be.

13:30.643 --> 13:35.137
Did you realize that was the ﬁrst party
where we didn't have to hide anything?

13:35.314 --> 13:38.852
I wish that us being married
meant we could always be that open.

13:39.026 --> 13:42.143
Part of a superhero marriage
is having two lives.

13:42.404 --> 13:45.146
I signed up for that when I said yes.

13:45.991 --> 13:49.279
Which is why I'm ﬁne if our relationship
has to take a backseat...

13:49.453 --> 13:50.989
...to your responsibilities.

13:52.414 --> 13:57.329
Lois, those responsibilities
have controlled my life way too long.

13:57.503 --> 14:03.419
And I— We can handle both
as long as we stay together.

14:03.634 --> 14:05.875
And I promise, we will.

14:08.681 --> 14:12.390
Well, then nothing can stop
Mr. and Mrs. Kent.

14:17.940 --> 14:19.680
Lane.

14:20.442 --> 14:21.943
Kent-Lane.

14:24.029 --> 14:26.441
I don't know. We'll ﬁgure it out.

14:29.118 --> 14:34.112
Hey, I signed up for a double life,
you signed up for news with ice cream.

14:34.290 --> 14:37.453
I'm a journalism junkie.
What are you gonna do?

14:37.626 --> 14:39.287
I get my own spoon.

14:45.593 --> 14:47.379
WOMAN [ON TV]:
The ﬁght broke out...

14:47.553 --> 14:50.795
...after Queen tackled an innocent man.
According to witnesses...

14:50.973 --> 14:53.180
-Oh, my God.
-...Queen was only deterred...

14:53.350 --> 14:56.308
-...when citizens came to the man's aid.
-Clark.

14:56.478 --> 14:59.140
lMtnesses claim Oliver Queen
and other vigilantes...

14:59.315 --> 15:02.978
...Ied an unprovoked attack against
people attempting a citizen 's arrest.

15:03.152 --> 15:05.734
Queen '8 disappearance
has sparked a citywide manhunt.

15:05.946 --> 15:07.482
A spokeswoman for the VRA....

15:07.656 --> 15:10.068
Guess the honeymoon's
ofﬁcially over.

15:11.660 --> 15:13.161
Go.

15:24.840 --> 15:26.671
CAT:
We should have run that photo.

15:26.842 --> 15:30.209
We would have, if you hadn't
played judge, jury and executioner.

15:30.387 --> 15:34.255
Not executioner. Editor. Your facts
weren't veriﬁed, your writing is juvenile.

15:34.475 --> 15:37.592
And you're losing subscriptions
while The Daily Star sells out.

15:37.770 --> 15:40.682
Face it, Tess, if you don't get
with the majority agenda soon...

15:40.856 --> 15:42.357
...someone's going to notice.

15:53.494 --> 15:55.701
-Tess Mercer.
-Yes.

15:58.040 --> 15:59.371
We need a few words.

15:59.541 --> 16:03.033
Then I suggest you call my ofﬁce
and make an appointment.

16:04.380 --> 16:06.211
We've already cleared your schedule.

16:32.449 --> 16:34.280
POLICEMAN:
Moving right.

16:41.083 --> 16:42.448
He's not here.

16:42.626 --> 16:44.287
Let's move.

16:44.837 --> 16:46.577
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

16:46.755 --> 16:49.588
[HELICOPTER DRONING]

16:49.758 --> 16:52.090
You gonna stitch that up yourself,
or call Emil?

16:52.261 --> 16:55.594
-You should see the other guys.
-I did. On television.

16:55.764 --> 16:56.970
Why didn't you call me?

16:59.101 --> 17:02.639
It's my fault. I ﬁgured you could use
some time alone with Lois.

17:03.272 --> 17:06.605
I told the human speed bag
you'd wanna know he got his bell rung.

17:07.109 --> 17:08.269
COURTNEY:
Wait a minute.

17:09.361 --> 17:12.273
I thought you said that Slade died
in the explosion.

17:12.448 --> 17:16.942
Like so many of you,
I am a victim of a vigilante attack.

17:17.119 --> 17:19.360
And while I was lucky enough...

17:19.580 --> 17:24.040
...to survive the explosion
caused by Oliver Queen...

17:24.209 --> 17:25.710
...it came at a cost.

17:25.878 --> 17:30.292
Too many civilians have been left
feeling unsafe in their own homes.

17:30.466 --> 17:32.673
Too many people have suffered...

17:32.843 --> 17:35.676
...while too few vigilantes
have been brought to justice.

17:35.846 --> 17:40.135
It's time these terrorists paid
for their crimes.

17:40.309 --> 17:42.300
It's time he pay for his.

17:42.478 --> 17:44.389
Yeah, well, there's only one problem.

17:44.605 --> 17:48.143
It's not just the government against us,
the people have turned on us too.

17:48.317 --> 17:51.400
lMth Slade alive, we can't exist.
He knows too much about us.

17:51.612 --> 17:55.696
So until Slade's been dealt with,
it's gotta be radio silence between us.

17:57.493 --> 17:59.074
We have to go underground.

17:59.244 --> 18:02.327
Our lives as we knew them are over.

18:02.915 --> 18:06.032
Courtney Whitmore, studying abroad.

18:06.210 --> 18:09.543
-Carter Hall, on sabbatical.
-And Clark Kent?

18:13.509 --> 18:14.589
Gone.

18:14.760 --> 18:17.502
Now we're all card-carrying members
of the fugitive club.

18:17.679 --> 18:20.671
We have to protect the secrets
we still have.

18:21.141 --> 18:23.382
So until it's safe...

18:24.937 --> 18:27.428
...l'm shutting down Watchtower.

18:36.865 --> 18:38.696
[ALARM RINGS]

18:56.468 --> 18:58.299
[HELICOPTER DRONING]

19:02.266 --> 19:04.757
GUARD:
Keys, coins, phone.

19:11.483 --> 19:13.144
WOMAN:
What a beautiful ring.

19:13.318 --> 19:15.274
Congratulations.

19:15.821 --> 19:19.405
-Military's not big on accessories, huh?
-Only if they're medals.

19:19.575 --> 19:20.655
[CHUCKLES]

19:20.826 --> 19:24.193
But a brat like you
should know that, Lois.

19:27.291 --> 19:31.580
Now, let's talk about the
extraordinary man who won your heart.

19:36.341 --> 19:40.004
Listen, you camo cop-out,
my father's a four-star general—

19:41.096 --> 19:44.429
Sam Lane's not the only general
who can lead an army, Lois.

20:00.032 --> 20:01.397
This is bad.

20:01.575 --> 20:04.442
Heightened security,
threat-level red bad.

20:14.838 --> 20:19.457
Lois, like I said, if you broke your phone
during that interview, just expense it.

20:21.637 --> 20:23.218
[EMIL CLEARS THROAT]

20:29.978 --> 20:32.560
[MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER RADIO]

20:35.150 --> 20:36.981
Fine, I will.

20:42.741 --> 20:45.278
Hope you got your stories straight.

20:47.162 --> 20:52.077
An unusually erratic schedule,
surprisingly short hours.

20:52.251 --> 20:56.335
How is it that you're afforded
such enviable ﬂexibility?

20:56.505 --> 20:59.963
Well, I'm a very valued member
of the staff...

21:00.133 --> 21:02.624
...and my work's not conﬁned
to the emergency room.

21:02.803 --> 21:04.293
Or the hospital.

21:04.513 --> 21:05.798
So where else do you work?

21:06.014 --> 21:09.757
Well, I'm sure that you've driven through
our lower-income neighborhoods.

21:09.935 --> 21:13.928
Or been made aware of the number
of households that lack health care?

21:14.106 --> 21:17.018
Are you trying to tell me
those missing hours were spent...

21:17.192 --> 21:18.978
...at free clinics helping the poor?

21:19.152 --> 21:22.690
I made an oath to help those in need
no matter who they are.

21:22.906 --> 21:27.525
Be they penniless
or rich as Oliver Queen.

21:28.537 --> 21:32.871
According to ﬁnancial records,
you've been on his payroll for years.

21:33.041 --> 21:35.453
If you're trying to imply
that I'm involved...

21:35.627 --> 21:38.710
...with terrorist activities
because of Oliver Queen's funding--

21:38.922 --> 21:41.038
Hey, you're a man of science,
Dr. Hamilton.

21:41.216 --> 21:43.878
You value truth,
so I'm gonna be truthful.

21:44.052 --> 21:46.839
Oliver Queen is relatively unimportant.

21:47.055 --> 21:50.968
The only assets of his
that we're interested in are his friends.

21:53.562 --> 21:54.972
What are their names?

21:55.147 --> 21:57.433
Their real ones.

22:04.448 --> 22:07.656
You've been making a name for yourself
in the news world, Lois.

22:07.826 --> 22:11.535
Women's lib got me pants and a fair
wage, I ﬁgured I'd make the most of it.

22:11.705 --> 22:14.412
Well, I hope your ﬁancé's
not the jealous type...

22:14.583 --> 22:17.666
...considering your close relationship
with the Blur.

22:17.836 --> 22:21.169
I wouldn't call the relationship between
people who never speak close.

22:21.340 --> 22:23.331
I'd call it nonexistent.

22:23.508 --> 22:27.092
Those articles have your name
in the byline, they're all about the Blur...

22:27.262 --> 22:28.763
...and they all have quotes.

22:29.348 --> 22:32.215
You wanna revise your claim
that you never speak?

22:36.104 --> 22:40.723
Or maybe we should just consider
all of that chat pillow talk.

22:43.111 --> 22:45.773
I want the Blur, Lois.

22:46.448 --> 22:50.782
You're not leaving this room
until I have Clark Kent.

23:04.716 --> 23:06.092
[DOOR OPENS]

23:06.259 --> 23:07.874
So much for going off the grid.

23:08.095 --> 23:10.552
Carter. What are you doing here?

23:10.722 --> 23:13.555
CARTER: Probably the same thing
as you, looking for answers.

23:13.725 --> 23:16.467
Besides, I've adopted a rule
over the centuries:

23:16.645 --> 23:18.977
Don't go underground until you're dead.

23:19.147 --> 23:21.638
We may not have a choice
unless I can ﬁx this.

23:22.901 --> 23:25.813
I promised Lois
she and I would be together.

23:26.029 --> 23:28.406
But what if we can't? I mean, literally.

23:28.615 --> 23:31.573
If her only relationship is with the Blur
and not Clark Kent...

23:31.743 --> 23:34.120
...I'm not sure what kind of marriage
that'll be.

23:34.287 --> 23:36.494
Don't tell me
you're canceling the wedding...

23:36.665 --> 23:40.829
...because I already started working
on a speech and it's looking good.

23:41.753 --> 23:43.493
You're not supposed to be here.

23:43.672 --> 23:47.335
You're not supposed to be here either,
so I guess that makes three of us.

23:47.551 --> 23:50.759
We're supposed to be heroes,
setting an example for the kids.

23:50.929 --> 23:53.045
We can't even follow orders.

23:53.682 --> 23:55.013
Even if we gave them.

23:55.183 --> 23:58.675
l was thinking about Slade
and that mega-mark-of-darkness thing.

23:58.854 --> 24:01.186
-Omega.
-Oh, whatever.

24:01.356 --> 24:05.520
Anyway, the darkness has to be driving
everything somehow, right?

24:05.694 --> 24:09.186
Because I've seen hatred before,
and I've never seen anything like this.

24:09.364 --> 24:11.355
Well, live long enough and you will.

24:11.575 --> 24:15.864
I've seen this level of hatred before,
in humanity's darkest hours.

24:16.079 --> 24:18.866
The Spanish Inquisition,
the Third Reich.

24:19.082 --> 24:22.540
-The darkness has been here before?
CARTER: Several times.

24:22.711 --> 24:26.545
Every time it looked like the world
would be consumed by hatred...

24:26.715 --> 24:30.173
...another force arose,
a much brighter one...

24:30.969 --> 24:32.709
...to send the darkness back.

24:32.888 --> 24:34.719
And you had something
to do with that?

24:37.184 --> 24:39.300
Well, this time it's us.

24:39.603 --> 24:41.559
And we need to start
by stopping Slade.

24:41.730 --> 24:44.062
Well, that's easier said than done.

24:44.232 --> 24:47.144
Justice isn't only blind right now,
it's broken.

24:47.319 --> 24:51.062
There's no way the authorities
will keep that dog in a cage.

24:52.741 --> 24:56.575
They won't, but I might have a place
to put him until we make things right.

24:56.745 --> 24:59.737
A place where he can't hurt anybody.

25:00.415 --> 25:02.747
If you know the Blur
and the other vigilantes...

25:02.918 --> 25:05.250
...then why aren't their faces
all over the news?

25:05.420 --> 25:09.083
A general's daughter and she doesn't
know the ﬁrst thing about strategy.

25:09.257 --> 25:12.420
Right now,
public opinion's in our favor, Lois.

25:12.636 --> 25:17.426
Yes, but if you start targeting civilians
without proof...

25:17.641 --> 25:20.132
...then you're not gonna be seen
as the good guys.

25:20.727 --> 25:23.434
I think what the public needs
is some truth.

25:23.647 --> 25:25.228
Front-page style.

25:25.857 --> 25:29.020
If you don't cooperate, you won't have
the chance to write that...

25:29.236 --> 25:31.227
...or any other article ever again.

25:36.618 --> 25:39.610
[POLICE SIRENS WAILING]

25:50.131 --> 25:52.338
You couldn't stare at me in my ofﬁce?

25:52.509 --> 25:55.171
I realize this room's a little cozy.

25:55.345 --> 25:57.210
You're trying
to make me uncomfortable.

25:58.848 --> 26:01.009
Why don't we just cut to the chase?

26:01.226 --> 26:03.683
Yes, I share letterhead
with Oliver Queen.

26:03.853 --> 26:05.468
No, I don't know where he is.

26:05.647 --> 26:08.810
You see, I work and he plays.

26:11.361 --> 26:14.649
And once upon a time
he played with you.

26:14.823 --> 26:17.690
Former lovers, now business partners.

26:17.867 --> 26:20.995
I'm willing to bet you share more
than a portfolio.

26:21.162 --> 26:24.700
I'm so sorry to disappoint you,
but for years our conversations...

26:24.874 --> 26:27.707
...have been limited to matters
that affect our investors.

26:27.877 --> 26:29.538
You're a good liar.

26:29.754 --> 26:31.369
But I've been watching.

26:31.548 --> 26:35.006
And I've issued enough "no comments"
to know when one really means:

26:35.176 --> 26:37.838
"I'm not telling."

26:40.849 --> 26:43.340
So where are the vigilantes?

26:46.771 --> 26:49.558
Come on, Tess, have something useful.

26:49.774 --> 26:52.265
An untapped phone.

26:53.903 --> 26:56.770
Some kind of ninja smoke bomb.

27:00.285 --> 27:01.866
Wait.

27:14.215 --> 27:17.548
l have got to get the name
of her custom-closet guy.

27:22.724 --> 27:24.260
It's just a slide.

27:24.434 --> 27:26.720
You love slides, Lois.

27:29.397 --> 27:31.809
I hate slides.

27:38.823 --> 27:40.438
Lois?

27:41.409 --> 27:42.740
I thought you were still—

27:42.911 --> 27:46.119
LOIS: Being questioned by Trotter
and her goose-stepping goons? Nope.

27:46.331 --> 27:49.289
Cleared of all charges.
So I thought I'd get back to work.

27:49.459 --> 27:53.793
Tess and her inquisition is no reason
to give up on the deadline rule.

27:53.963 --> 27:57.797
That's not in the employee handbook.
And I've read it cover to cover.

27:57.967 --> 27:59.093
You escaped.

27:59.260 --> 28:01.922
And you totally ratted us out to Trotter,
didn't you?

28:02.097 --> 28:05.430
Doing my civic duty. Just like
marching you back to the authorities.

28:05.600 --> 28:07.465
No, you are not.

28:07.644 --> 28:10.602
I need to ﬁnd Tess and Emil
and then get out of here.

28:11.231 --> 28:14.940
Please, Cat.
We have to put this ﬁre out, not fuel it.

28:15.110 --> 28:18.273
The people that the government
is targeting, they are not villains.

28:18.446 --> 28:21.938
They're heroes and they're putting
their lives on the line to protect us.

28:23.493 --> 28:27.452
Look, I know I don't say this ever...

28:27.622 --> 28:30.989
...but you are a good reporter,
that means your instincts are solid--

28:31.167 --> 28:33.158
My instincts are telling me
to turn you in.

28:33.378 --> 28:36.791
No, Cat. This isn't about me
or even you. Think about your son.

28:36.965 --> 28:39.206
What kind of hero
do you want him to believe in?

28:39.384 --> 28:41.420
The kind that destroys others
in the name of good...

28:41.594 --> 28:44.381
...or the kind that saves them
and lives up to the name?

28:45.306 --> 28:48.798
You're asking me to change everything
I believe about the world.

28:50.019 --> 28:52.146
Or rethink who you call a hero.

28:52.814 --> 28:57.148
What if I told you the Blur has saved you
at least twice without you knowing it?

28:58.278 --> 29:02.362
I know you love your son. And the only
reason that he still has a mother...

29:02.532 --> 29:07.652
...is because the man she says
is a bad guy actually saved her life.

29:07.829 --> 29:09.820
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

29:11.416 --> 29:13.031
Cat.

29:15.795 --> 29:17.660
Lois Lane. Have you seen her?

29:21.551 --> 29:26.170
No, Sergeant Garcia.
But if I do, I'll let you know right away.

29:34.230 --> 29:36.562
Thank you for that.

29:36.733 --> 29:38.940
Wait.

29:41.946 --> 29:45.063
Maybe everything's not
as black and white as I thought.

29:47.535 --> 29:52.029
I overheard Trotter say Slade's found
a new way to take care of the vigi--

29:52.874 --> 29:54.580
The heroes.

29:54.751 --> 29:56.912
Now that Oliver Queen's
been found guilty--

29:57.086 --> 30:00.328
They're gonna use him
to track down the others.

30:02.717 --> 30:05.709
Who knows what they'll ﬁnd
if they dig even deeper?

30:05.887 --> 30:06.922
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

30:07.096 --> 30:08.711
If you're gonna make
your move, Clark...

30:08.890 --> 30:12.223
...you might wanna make it quick,
because Slade already has.

30:19.359 --> 30:20.895
Operation Icarus?

30:21.069 --> 30:24.061
The Icarus myth is about fallen heroes
who reached too far.

30:24.239 --> 30:26.446
It's the only ﬁle ﬂagged for encryption.

30:26.616 --> 30:31.406
It's a blacklist of known and suspected
vigilantes and vigilante supporters...

30:31.579 --> 30:36.118
-...to be brought in for questioning.
-Tess, Lois and Emil...

30:36.292 --> 30:39.455
...are Slade's top draft choices
for this season of interrogation.

30:39.629 --> 30:42.587
They're uploading video ﬁles
every two hours.

30:42.757 --> 30:45.794
Clark, you're not gonna like
the latest ones. Come here.

30:50.098 --> 30:51.929
It's the Daily Planet.

30:52.100 --> 30:54.933
They're using
our own security systems against us.

31:00.525 --> 31:02.311
-Really?
-I miss my typewriter.

31:02.527 --> 31:04.768
You miss the telegraph.

31:05.029 --> 31:07.771
Just get away, 8-track.

31:07.949 --> 31:10.110
If Slade got access
to Daily Planet cameras...

31:10.285 --> 31:12.150
...he's using other cameras
across the city.

31:12.328 --> 31:13.443
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

31:15.164 --> 31:18.122
Look at this.
Try all the cameras across the city.

31:18.293 --> 31:21.956
And Big Brother Slade's hitting
a little too close to home for me.

31:22.130 --> 31:24.166
That's my ofﬁce.

31:36.978 --> 31:39.469
Sheppard, why don't I see Lane
back in your custody?

31:39.647 --> 31:43.060
Ma'am, we're still searching the building
and the surrounding areas.

31:43.693 --> 31:46.526
Take them to the secured location.

31:46.696 --> 31:48.357
Yes, ma'am.

31:51.075 --> 31:53.031
TESS: You don't wanna parade us
through the lobby?

31:53.202 --> 31:54.703
Or does kidnapping make
for bad press?

31:54.871 --> 31:56.031
SHEPPARD:
Shut up.

31:56.205 --> 31:57.285
[AIR WHOOSH ES]

31:57.457 --> 31:59.368
[GUARDS THUDDING AND GRUNTING]

31:59.584 --> 32:01.165
Where's Lois?

32:01.336 --> 32:03.076
Where is she?

32:22.649 --> 32:25.356
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

32:27.737 --> 32:30.228
-Oh, my God.
-When you do the ﬁnal on a building...

32:30.490 --> 32:33.106
...you never know
what you're gonna ﬁnd.

32:34.035 --> 32:37.744
Lois Lane, where's Clark Kent?

32:37.914 --> 32:40.405
I don't know. Besides,
you're way off target if you think he—

32:40.625 --> 32:42.206
[GRUNTS]

32:42.377 --> 32:45.210
-Try again.
-GI Joe, when are you going to accept...

32:45.380 --> 32:48.247
...that you can't beat
the real American heroes?

32:48.633 --> 32:52.091
Last time you tried,
you went down with the ship. Unh.

32:52.261 --> 32:53.341
[GLASS BREAKING]

32:53.513 --> 32:55.424
But I failed to take out my target.

32:55.640 --> 32:59.599
Luckily, fate and Uncle Sam's
advanced military tech...

32:59.769 --> 33:02.101
...gave me a second chance to do it.

33:02.271 --> 33:04.762
Family takes care of itself.

33:05.024 --> 33:08.562
And for better or for worse,
I am standing by the Blur.

33:08.736 --> 33:13.230
But he's not here
to stand between you and a bullet.

33:13.574 --> 33:16.407
No. No, wait.

33:18.162 --> 33:19.242
You win.

33:19.414 --> 33:21.450
That's my girl.

33:21.666 --> 33:24.248
I'm not your girl. I'm his.

33:26.087 --> 33:28.078
[LOIS GRUNTING]

33:28.256 --> 33:31.168
Wrong answer.

33:36.305 --> 33:37.761
[AIR WHOOSH ES]

34:08.504 --> 34:11.291
[BOTH GRUNTING]

34:36.741 --> 34:38.652
[SWORD SQUELCHES]

34:50.171 --> 34:52.002
lib}

35:17.865 --> 35:19.856
POLICEMAN:
Get him on the radio, seal that exit.

35:20.034 --> 35:23.026
[ALARM BLARING]

35:28.042 --> 35:33.082
l was wondering how long you'd hide
and let your friends take the fall.

35:35.883 --> 35:38.750
-You were in it. How did you--?
-Survive?

35:38.928 --> 35:41.920
Let's just say
the reaper can swing his sickle at me...

35:42.181 --> 35:44.672
...but I'm beyond death's stroke now.

35:45.184 --> 35:46.264
Where's Lois?

35:46.435 --> 35:49.427
Your problem is you think
other people deﬁne your life...

35:49.689 --> 35:52.396
...but the truth is,
they just get in the way.

35:52.567 --> 35:55.730
You don't believe that.
I know you had a family before.

35:55.903 --> 36:00.738
A soldier can ﬁght for others,
but he cannot afford to love them.

36:00.908 --> 36:03.570
You and I don't need to ﬁght, Clark.

36:03.744 --> 36:06.736
Let them go. Come and join me.

36:06.914 --> 36:09.405
We can put all this to an end.

36:11.919 --> 36:13.295
Never.

36:13.462 --> 36:16.590
You know,
when I named this operation Icarus...

36:16.757 --> 36:18.918
...it was because I believed...

36:19.093 --> 36:24.133
...that your fall would ultimately come
from your faith in your own invincibility.

36:24.974 --> 36:31.140
But then to actually see a man
with burning wings...

36:31.355 --> 36:32.470
...plummet from the sky....

36:32.648 --> 36:34.730
[CHUCKLING]

36:35.109 --> 36:38.442
God, I do enjoy the irony.

36:38.613 --> 36:40.444
What did you do?

36:43.284 --> 36:45.741
-Where are they?
-Dead.

36:47.788 --> 36:49.494
-You're lying.
-You know I'm not.

36:49.665 --> 36:53.658
Because a true soldier does
whatever it takes to ﬁnish the mission.

36:54.253 --> 36:56.289
Then consider this ﬁnished.

37:17.401 --> 37:18.937
Carter.

37:23.783 --> 37:27.025
CARTER:
Good. You're here.

37:27.203 --> 37:29.159
l have something for you.

37:30.581 --> 37:32.162
[CARTER GRUNTS]

37:37.755 --> 37:39.461
Lois.

37:41.550 --> 37:44.542
What happened? You okay?

37:44.720 --> 37:46.585
He saved me.

37:46.764 --> 37:48.800
He saved me.

37:51.686 --> 37:53.392
I'll get you help, okay?

37:53.562 --> 37:55.974
No, it's too late.

37:57.733 --> 37:58.984
Hey.

37:59.193 --> 38:01.980
I'm a pro at dying, remember?

38:03.698 --> 38:05.905
I should have been there, Carter.
I'm sorry.

38:06.075 --> 38:08.817
Can't always be you, Clark.

38:09.704 --> 38:12.116
This is all of our ﬁght.

38:15.209 --> 38:16.289
Listen.

38:18.212 --> 38:19.452
Listen.

38:20.339 --> 38:22.796
This is what we do.

38:24.468 --> 38:26.925
And my passing means...

38:27.847 --> 38:30.213
...I'll be with Shayera again.

38:32.143 --> 38:35.931
I owe you so much,
I don't know how to begin to thank you.

38:43.738 --> 38:45.103
You just did.

38:49.577 --> 38:51.738
You hold on to her.

38:52.872 --> 38:55.079
Because there has to be a balance,
Clark.

38:56.250 --> 39:01.495
We can't do what we have to do
if there's an emptiness in our heart.

39:04.008 --> 39:05.794
You remember that.

39:05.968 --> 39:07.799
I will, I promise.

39:10.056 --> 39:14.390
Oh, I am sorry I won't be there
to help you ﬁght the darkness.

39:19.690 --> 39:22.807
But you have all the help you need.

39:29.533 --> 39:31.194
Carter?

39:39.335 --> 39:42.327
[POLICE SIRENS WAILING
IN DISTANCE]

42:19.370 --> 42:21.361
[English - US - SDH]
